WHO: Jennifer M. Adams Center for Ocean-Land-Atmosphere Studies (COLA)

Dear Experts,
I have been happily using the RegridWeightGen tool to regrid POP ocean model output to a regualar lat/lon grid. Now I have a new native grid from the CESM CAM output (ne30 -- a cube sphere that is presented as a 1-D array) that looks like this:

netcdf spcesm_b1850-2000_ne30_g16.cam.h0.1850-01 {
dimensions:
        ncol = 48602 ;
variables:
        double lat(ncol) ;
                lat:long_name = "latitude" ;
                lat:units = "degrees_north" ;
        double area(ncol) ;
        double lon(ncol) ;
                lon:long_name = "longitude" ;
                lon:units = "degrees_east" ;
        float TS(time, ncol) ;
                TS:units = "K" ;
                TS:long_name = "Surface temperature (radiative)" ;
                TS:cell_methods = "time: mean" ;

Will RegridWeightGen handle this as a source grid? I tried the following command and the process just hung with no log file and no output. I'm not certain that the src_type GRIDSPEC is correct in this case. 

> ./ESMF_RegridWeightGen -i -p none -s spcesm_b1850-2000_ne30_g16.cam.h0.1850-01.nc --src_type GRIDSPEC \
--src_coordinates lon,lat -d linear0p5.nc -w weights.nc


> ./ESMF_RegridWeightGen --version
   ESMF_VERSION_STRING:       5.3.1 beta snapshot
   ESMF_VERSION_MAJOR:                   5
   ESMF_VERSION_MINOR:                   3
   ESMF_VERSION_REVISION:                1
   ESMF_VERSION_PATCHLEVEL:              0
   ESMF_VERSION_PUBLIC:        F
   ESMF_VERSION_BETASNAPSHOT:  T

My ESMF_RegridWeightGen is built with netcdf version 4.1.3. 
Thanks!
--Jennifer


--
Jennifer M. Adams
