WHO: Jennifer M. Adams Center for Ocean-Land-Atmosphere Studies (COLA)

Hi, Peggy -- 
I have another source grid I need to interpolate to a regular lat/lon. The grid is from a high-res run of the POP model at 0.1-degree resolution. Here is the edited ncdump output:

netcdf HRC06.pop.h1.0101-04 {
dimensions:
nlon = 3600 ;
nlat = 2400 ;
variables:
double ULONG(nlat, nlon) ;
ULONG:long_name = "array of u-grid longitudes" ;
ULONG:units = "degrees_east" ;
double ULAT(nlat, nlon) ;
ULAT:long_name = "array of u-grid latitudes" ;
ULAT:units = "degrees_north" ;
double TLONG(nlat, nlon) ;
TLONG:long_name = "array of t-grid longitudes" ;
TLONG:units = "degrees_east" ;
double TLAT(nlat, nlon) ;
TLAT:long_name = "array of t-grid latitudes" ;
TLAT:units = "degrees_north" ;
}

My destination grid is linear, 3600x1800. I ran this command:

> ESMF_RegridWeightGen -i -p none -s HRC06.pop.h1.0101-04.nc --src_type GRIDSPEC \
--src_coordinates TLONG,TLAT -d linear0p5.nc -w weights.nc

It has been running for over three hours and the logfile is empty (0 bytes) and I don't know whether it is working or hung. The output I got to the terminal when I began did not indicate any problems. Have I done something wrong, or is it just taking so long because of the high-res grids in use? 
--Jennifer







--
Jennifer M. Adams
