4400 University Drive
Fairfax, VA 22030

WHO: Cedric Ody from SHOM (Hydrographic and Oceanographic Service of the Navy) France

Dear developpers,

I am planning to use the ESMF regridding application to calculate the weights that are necessary for a conservative interpolation of bathymetric data. [and later for data forcing interpolation.]

I have set up the library version 6.2 on my debian lenny 32 bits. I was checking the calculation of areas on a very simple test.

This simple test consists of single equal destination and source elements. These elements differ only in that they do not overlay exactly but one is slided left/right of the other one. More precisely, I have an element of two degrees width and the length of overlay is exactly one degree.

I understood that when using the option --user_areas, the software should use the area given by the user. I am using ESMF format and set up the field elementArea in my file (which is equal to 7.8e-4). However, the files containing the generated weights are the same wether or not I set the option. And the areas in the files are 5.e-4 which probably correspond to the great circle area of my elements.

I can clearly check on the log that I have not made any mistake in typing the option because I can read that the soft is going to use the give weights (please see below the log, the destination file and the weight file).

Could you please tell me what I am missing?

Thank you,

Cédric


